{{WPMIXInfobox | iba = | name = The Vod-Bomb | image = VodkaRedBull.jpg | caption = A Vod-Bomb in a plastic cup | type = cocktail | flaming = | vodka = yes | served = [[ice cube|On the rocks]], or [[straight up (bartending)|Straight up]] | garnish = | drinkware = highball | ingredients = *3 oz. [[vodka]] *1 can [[Red Bull]] | prep = Either mix together, with or without ice, or drop a shot of vodka into the Red Bull in the style of [[depth charge (cocktail)|Depth charge]] }}
An alcoholic drink most commonly known as a '''VRB'''. Also known as a '''Vod-Bomb''',<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/31/weekinreview/31bruni.html | title=Caffeine and Alcohol: Wham! Bam! Boozled. | work=The New York Times | date=October 10, 2010 | accessdate=September 11, 2011 | author=Bruni, Frank}}</ref> '''Birch''', '''Vod Bull''', or a 'DVR' ('''d'''ouble '''v'''odka '''r'''ed bull), it is a [[cocktail]] made by mixing [[vodka]] and the caffeinated energy drink [[Red Bull]]. It is generally popular among 18â30 year olds in bars and nightclubs around the world.<ref name="MosherAkins2007">{{cite book|author1=Clayton James Mosher|author2=Scott Akins|title=Drugs and drug policy: the control of consciousness alteration|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=aDMvoMxx0-IC|accessdate=11 September 2011|year=2007|publisher=SAGE|isbn=978-0-7619-3007-5|pp=71}}</ref> Red Bull has been used as mixer in Europe since the 1990s, but the drink became especially popular in North America in the 21st century.<ref name="Swierczynski2003">{{cite book|author=Duane Swierczynski|title=The Perfect Drink for Every Occasion: 151 Cocktails That Will Freshen Your Breath, Impress a Hot Date, Cure a Hangover, and More!|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=uqtmCO0dpBMC|accessdate=11 September 2011|date=1 June 2003|publisher=Quirk Books|isbn=978-1-931686-29-7|pp=92}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.cbc.ca/marketplace/pre-2007/files/health/redbull/alcohol.html | title=Mixed messages: Alcohol and Red Bull | work=CBC Marketplace | date=February 5, 2011 | accessdate=September 11, 2011}}</ref>
The ratio of Vodka to Red Bull varies widely, but is usually around 2:3.<ref name="AML">{{cite web|url=http://www.drinknation.com/drink/vodka-red-bull |title=Vodka Red Bull recipe |publisher=Drinknation.com |date= |accessdate=2009-10-29}}</ref> In some places it is customary to serve an entire can with a single shot of vodka, in others a can may be split between several glasses, each containing several shots of vodka. The Red Bull dominates so that the flavor of the alcohol is not too strong.
[[Energy_drink#Caffeinated_alcoholic_energy_drinks|Caffeinated alcoholic energy drinks]] can be hazardous, as caffeine can mask the influence of alcohol and may lead a person to misinterpret their actual level of intoxication.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/health/article-491765/Mixing-vodka-Red-Bull-deadly-warn-experts.html | title=Mixing vodka and Red Bull can be deadly, warn experts | work=The Daily Mail | date=November 2007 | accessdate=September 11, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://abcnews.go.com/Health/Wellness/dangers-alcoholic-energy-drinks/story?id=13384522 | title=Mixing Alcohol and Caffeine Makes Drinkers Feel More Impulsive, Says Study | work=ABC News | date=April 15, 2011 | accessdate=September 11, 2011}}</ref> It was reported in Sweden that two people died after drinking Vodka Red Bull. The Swedish National Food Administration is investigating and has issued a public warning, telling people not to drink Red Bull mixed with alcohol or after heavy exercise.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/health/1435409.stm|title=Red Bull in suspected link to deaths | work=BBC News | date=2001-07-12 | accessdate=2010-01-06}}</ref>
